USAGE

Installation and Setup
Before using FBS (formerly fasta-basic-stats), you need to download and install the package. Follow these steps:

1. Clone or download the repository from GitHub:
Run
git clone https://github.com/didieranoh/fasta_basic_stats.git
cd fasta_basic_stats

2. (Optional but recommended) Create a Python virtual environment:
Run
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate      # Mac/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate         # Windows

3. Install the package in editable mode so you can run it as a command-line tool:
Run
pip install -e .

4. Check Installation worked
Run 
fbs --help


BASIC COMMAND USGAE

fbs -i path/to/input.fasta

or fbs -i path/to/input.fasta  -o custum/name 

Arguments:
-i / --input → required: Path to the FASTA file
-o / --output → Optional: Custom base name for the report files


This will:
Print a full report to the terminal
Save a TXT report named: custom/name.txt in the same folder as the input file

You can find an example .fna file in Example files

Notes
Reports are saved in the same directory as the input FASTA file by default
Use the -o option to customize the report name
Ensure your FASTA files are properly formatted to avoid errors
